Adjust rack to middle position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Bring a large #pot{} of @salt{} water to a boil. Line a #baking sheet{} with foil and lightly oil. Wash and dry all produce. Cut @Roma Tomato{2} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Zest and quarter @Lemon{1}. In a #small bowl{}, combine @Panko Breadcrumbs{½%cup}, half the @Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon}, half the @Parmesan Cheese{½%cup}, and 1 TBSP @Olive Oil{4%teaspoon}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Toss tomatoes on one side of prepared #sheet{} with half the garlic and a drizzle of olive oil. Season with salt and pepper; arrange skin sides down. Pat @Chicken Breasts{12%ounce} dry with paper towels and season all over with remaining Fry Seasoning, salt, and pepper; place on empty side of same sheet. In a second small bowl, combine @Dijon Mustard{2%teaspoon} and @Sour Cream{2%tablespoon}; evenly spread onto tops of chicken. Mound coated sides with panko mixture, pressing to adhere (no need to coat the undersides).

Roast tomatoes and chicken on middle rack until tomatoes are lightly browned and softened and chicken is cooked through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> TIP: If tomatoes are still firm, remove chicken from sheet and continue roasting tomatoes.

Once water is boiling, add @Spaghetti{6%ounce} to pot. Cook until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

Melt 1 TBSP @Butter{2%tablespoon} in pot used for pasta over medium heat. Add remaining garlic; cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Lower heat; stir in @Cream Cheese{2%tablespoon}, a pinch of lemon zest, another 1 TBSP butter (2 TBSP for 4 servings), and ¼ cup reserved pasta cooking water until smooth. Squeeze in 1 TBSP lemon juice; add spaghetti and toss to combine.

> TIP: If needed, stir in more pasta cooking water a splash at a time until pasta is coated in a creamy sauce.

Add half the tomatoes to pot with spaghetti. Season with salt and pepper; toss to combine. Divide pasta and chicken between plates. Top pasta with remaining tomatoes and Parmesan. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.